The paper deals with natural language processing tasks such as entity linking and entity typing, which are typically studied in the subfield of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The use of neural models and distant supervision also suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves working with large datasets and deriving types from categories, which could be relevant to database systems (cs.DB). Finally, the use of hyperlinked mentions in Wikipedia suggests a connection to information retrieval (cs.IR).
